# Lexora AI — Development Rules

Read full doc: `docs/engineering/development-rules.md`

## Task workflow

1. Pick **one task** from `docs/product/phases/` (ID e.g. `P1-T001`)
2. Branch: `p1/P1-T001-short-description` (Phase 0 docs: stay on `main`)
3. Implement **only** that task's scope — **finish code first**
4. **Add or update automated test case(s)** for the change (unit / integration / E2E)
5. **Run automation locally — all must pass before commit**
6. **Auto-commit when finish** — commit immediately when DoD met (same session)
7. **Push immediately after commit** — do not leave finished work unpushed
8. Mark task ✅ in the phase plan file (include in same commit when possible)

## Auto-commit rule (mandatory)

When task DoD is complete, **you MUST** run `git commit` and `git push` before ending your turn.

```
Finish code → Write/update tests → Run automation → Pass? → Commit → Push → Mark ✅
                                      ↓ fail
                                   Fix — do not commit or push
```

| Rule | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Never** | Stop with finished uncommitted work |
| **Never** | Ask user to commit a completed task |
| **Never** | Batch multiple task IDs in one commit |
| **Phase 0 docs** | Commit + **push directly to `main`** (allowed) |
| **Sprint 1+ code** | Commit + push task branch → open PR |

**Blockers only:** no git auth, no network — report blocker; still commit locally if push fails.

## Test automation rule (required)

| Change | Required test |
|---|---|
| `lib/modules/*` | Unit test |
| `app/api/v1/*` | Integration test |
| UI / user flow | E2E spec + `npm run test:e2e:smoke` |
| Bug fix | Regression test |
| Docs only | No tests — commit when doc DoD met |

**Never push** code with failing local tests. CI is a second gate, not a replacement.

## Commit format (strict — enforced by CI)

```
{task-id}: {content}
```

**Rules:**
- Single line only — no body, no `Co-authored-by`, no AI tool attribution
- Regex: `^(P0-T\d+|P1-T\d+|P1C-T\d+|P2-T\d+|P3-T\d+): [a-z0-9][a-z0-9 /-]{2,71}$`
- Lowercase imperative, no trailing period, 3–72 chars
- **One task = one commit** — branch task ID must match commit task ID
- PR title must equal commit message
- Use canonical commit message from phase plan when listed

**Forbidden in commits:** `WIP`, `Co-authored-by`, `Generated-by`, `model`, `fine-tune`, `training`, `trainer`, emojis, generic words (`fix`, `update`, `misc`)

Examples:
- `P1-T001: scaffold Next.js modular monolith`
- `P0-T02: complete Azure speech engine spike`

Never combine task IDs. **Amend forbidden after push** — fix forward with new task commit.

## Code (MVP)

- Next.js 15 modular monolith: logic in `lib/modules/*`, thin `app/api/v1/` routes
- MongoDB + Mongoose, TypeScript strict
- AI keys server-side only; prompts from `docs/AI/`
- Follow `docs/engineering/tech-stack.md` and ADR

## Before commit (code tasks)

```bash
npm run lint && npm run typecheck && npm run test
npm run test:e2e:smoke   # if UI or user flow changed (after P1-T099)
```

## Git

- **Phase 0:** direct commit + **push to `main` allowed** until M0
- **Sprint 1+:** task branch + PR — no direct push to `main`
- PR title: `{task-id}: {description}` — validated by GitHub Actions (P1-T104)
- All CI checks must pass + 1 human approval before merge (see `ci-cd.md`)
- No secrets in repo
- No force push to `main`
- No `--no-verify` unless TL approves

Adjustments require Technical Lead approval.

**Commit messages:** strict task format only — no AI/model/trainer attribution. **Auto-commit + push when task is done.**
